com.parrot.arsdk.arstream

Class ARStreamReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.parrot.arsdk.arstream.ARStreamReader

  • public class ARStreamReader
extends Object
    Wrapper class for the ARSTREAM_Reader C object.

    To create an ARStreamReader, the application must provide a suitable ARStreamReaderListener to handle the events.

    The two ARStreamReader Runnables must be run in independant threads

      • ARStreamReader

        public ARStreamReader(ARNetworkManager netManager,
                      int dataBufferId,
                      int ackBufferId,
                      ARNativeData initialFrameBuffer,
                      ARStreamReaderListener theEventListener,
                      int maxFragmentSize,
                      int maxAckInterval)
        Constructor for ARStreamReader object
        Create a new instance of an ARStreamReader for a given ARNetworkManager, and given buffer ids within the ARNetworkManager.
        Parameters:
        netManager - The ARNetworkManager to use (must be initialized and valid)
        dataBufferId - The id to use for data transferts on network (must be a valid buffer id in netManager
        ackBufferId - The id to use for ack transferts on network (must be a valid buffer id in netManager
        initialFrameBuffer - The first frame buffer to use
        theEventListener - The event listener to use for this instance
        maxFragmentSize - Maximum allowed size for a video data fragment. Video frames larger that will be fragmented.

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stops the internal threads of the ARStreamReader.
        Calling this function allow the ARStreamReader Runnables to end

      • dispose

        public boolean dispose()
        Deletes the ARStreamReader.
        This function should only be called after stop()

        Warning: If this function returns false, then the ARStreamReader was not disposed !
        Returns:
        true if the Runnables are not running.
        false if the ARStreamReader could not be disposed now.
